      <h2>About Kherin Trufina</h2>
      <p>Kherin Trufina is a dedicated and passionate law student currently pursuing her B.Com., LL.B at SASTRA University (2023–2028). Born and raised in Karumandapam, Trichy, Kherin has always been deeply curious about justice, truth, and the workings of the legal system — with a strong focus on criminal law, her area of interest and specialization.</p>
      <p>She comes from a humble and hardworking background. Her father, Arockiaraj, is both a tea stall owner and a real estate businessman, whose relentless commitment and values have played a key role in shaping her aspirations. From her formative school years to stepping into the field of law, Kherin’s journey has been guided by discipline, resilience, and a continuous desire for personal and professional growth.</p>
      <p>Kherin strongly believes that every individual deserves to be heard and that every story holds value. Her vision is to use law not just as a profession but as a powerful tool for empowerment, advocacy, and justice.</p>
